definitions.definition: Characterised by or exhibiting a change in form or character .
Pertaining to metamorphism ; having been structurally altered as a result of, or resulting from, exposure to intense heat and/or pressure (at the contact zone between colliding plates, for example).
Of or relating to the Metamorphic Technique , a form of massage influenced by reflexology .

main_definition: Characterised by or exhibiting a change in form or character . [from 19th c.]
